    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Union types allow a variable to hold multiple possible types using the '|' operator."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Union Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "let id: string | number;\nid = 101;\nid = 'ABC';"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are Intersection Types?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Intersection types combine multiple types into one using the '&' operator, requiring all properties."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Intersection Example"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "typescript",
      "value": "type A = { name: string };\ntype B = { age: number };\n\ntype Person = A & B;"
    },
